summary: Humpty Dumpty is a famous character from an English nursery rhyme. He's usually shown as a talking egg, though the rhyme never says that directly. The rhyme was first written down in the late 1700s in England. Its exact origins are unknown, but it's one of the most well-known rhymes in English. Humpty Dumpty became even more popular in the U.S. through a Broadway show in the 1860s. He's also famous for his appearance in Lewis Carroll's book "Through the Looking-Glass."
title: Humpty Dumpty
